    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @spindriftwebs Thanks for your patience. I can't reproduce the error. I selected funboard and the url is correctly updated. I can't manage to have a car as you proposed in the example. Can you give me the scenario that you follow on your page?\r\n\r\nTo sum up your use case, you want to store the URL of the current search so the users can go back to it?\r\n\r\nWhat about you could save the complete state of the search and send it to your backend? You can do this with those lines:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// extract the state\r\nvar state = search.helper.getState();\r\n\r\n// initialize instantsearch with a state\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n  // ... other parameters here\r\n  searchParameters: state\r\n});\r\n```",
