  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Sorry about the late answer. I appreciate your patience, thanks.\r\n\r\nSo if you want to leverage the same search in the backend, you could use the JS Helper [getQuery](https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-helper-js/blob/develop/src/algoliasearch.helper.js#L135-L138). It's not documented but it will give you the Algolia query that you can reuse in the backend for the hits.\r\n\r\nHowever you won't be able to use that back in the front-end. You would have to save the state using `getState` for that.",
